Package: OmicsBatchR
Title: Comprehensive Batch Correction and Benchmarking for Single-Cell and Bulk Omics Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Divya", "Mishra", 
           email = "panomiq@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")),
    person("Panomiq Bioinformatics Team", 
           role = c("aut"))
  )
Description: OmicsBatchR provides a unified interface to run, compare, and benchmark 
    multiple batch correction methods for single-cell and bulk RNA-seq data. 
    Supported methods include Harmony, Seurat CCA, scVI, ComBat/ComBat-seq, 
    BBKNN, Scanorama, and FastMNN. The package includes automatic best-method 
    selection based on LISI and kBET benchmarking scores, and generates 
    publication-ready PCA/UMAP comparison plots for all methods.
